								<p>Looking for a co-founder? You should start this process by first looking at yourself. What are your core strengths and skills? What about your weaknesses? Co-founders can help complement your skills, help you manage your time more effectively, and provide moral support. But the decision to bring on new co-founders shouldn't be taken lightly. The following guide will walk you through why finding the right co-founder is so important and what you need to do to find the right one(s). Ultimately, building a cohesive team will put you one step closer to executing your startup idea. </p>

								<h2>What is the perfect startup team?</h2>

								<p>Saul Klein, serial tech entrepreneur, believes that the perfect startup team has three types of founders working together: <br>
								1. Someone who understands how to build technologies and systems to solve problems;<br>
								2. Someone who understands the human factors behind those problems, why they exist, what it takes to fix them and how to shape the experience;<br>
								3. Someone who understands how to reach, talk to and sell to the people whose problems are being solved - and keep finding more of them</p>

